headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 36 points and sparked closing 9-0 run to help the Milwaukee Bucks rally to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 105-100 on Sunday for their fifth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Bucks rally late to to beat Clippers 105-100

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum made two twisting, driving baskets in the final 15 seconds and finished with 31 points Sunday night, leading the Boston Celtics to a 111-110 comeback victory over the Washington Wizards despite 46 points by Bradley Beal.

events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 17 of his 25 points in the second half and the New York Knicks moved above .500 with a 109-90 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks above .500 after 109-90 rout of Pistons

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat are back at .500, not even a couple weeks removed from being near the very bottom of the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat top Hawks for 6th straight win, get back to .500

headlines.description: — Justise Winslow scored 20 points and the Memphis Grizzles pounded Houston 133-84 on Sunday night for the Rockets' 11th straight loss.

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Lakers blew a 14-point, fourth-quarter lead in their first meeting against the Golden State Warriors. They were determined not to let that happen Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 19 in 1,300th regular-season game in Lakers win

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 21 of his season-high 43 points in the third quarter to carry Phoenix in a 118-99 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Sunday night, the 14th win for the Suns in their last 17 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 43 points, surging Suns beat T-wolves 118-99

headlines.description: — PJ Washington scored a career-high 42 points, Malik Monk converted a three-point play with 1.4 seconds remaining and the Charlotte Hornets stunned the Sacramento Kings 127-126 with a late rally Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk's three-point play helps Hornets stun Kings 127-126
